# ANTIGRAVITY AGENT INSTRUCTIONS & CONSTRAINTS

This ruleset is executed/loaded automatically by the Antigravity agent before performing any instructions or code changes.

---

## 🚨 1. COMMAND & RUNTIME CONSTRAINTS (CRITICAL)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **NEVER RUN LOCAL SERVERS/NO LOCALHOST RUNS FIRST AND LAST**: Do not start local servers (`npm run dev`, `npm start`, python HTTP servers, etc.) or open localhost ports at the start, during, or end of execution under any circumstances.
> - **ALWAYS FOLLOW AC'S FIRST**: Prioritize satisfying all Acceptance Criteria (AC) listed in this document and [PAGE_AC.md](file:///c:/Users/viksingh44/Pictures/my-learning-portal/PAGE_AC.md) before considering a task finished.
> - **SINGLE PERMISSION REQUEST**: Request all needed permissions in one single prompt at the start of the task. Do not continuously block or prompt for minor filesystem/command approvals throughout execution.
> - **ALL-IN-ONE FIX DELIVERY**: Analyze, implement, and verify all code changes, layout standardizations, and bug fixes at once in a single turn. Do not break simple fixes into multiple incremental updates requiring intermediate approvals.

- **NEVER RUN LOCAL SERVERS / DEPLOY SERVERS**: Do not execute command-line instructions that attempt to bind network ports or run local listener processes.
- **NO LOCALHOST WEB AUTOMATION / TESTING**: Do not run or command localhost operations.
- **ALLOWED SCOPE**: Focus edits strictly on the files directly causing or related to the reported issue.
- **PRESERVE EXTRA SECTIONS**: If a page contains extra sections or flows with valid educational/technical details, do not delete them. Instead, preserve them by refactoring or merging the content into the 8 standard layout components (e.g., adding tabs in the Mock Code Editor, items in the Q&A accordion, keywords in the Glossary, etc.). Only delete redundant, duplicated, or completely irrelevant placeholder/out-of-scope content.

---

## 📋 2. KEY ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA (AC) CHECKLIST

Always verify that the learning portals satisfy these criteria from [PAGE_AC.md](file:///c:/Users/viksingh44/Pictures/my-learning-portal/PAGE_AC.md):
- **AC 1: Session Switching**: Only one session topic is visible. Tabs switch sessions instantly. Progress dots (green for done, blue for active, gray for remaining) must paint correctly.
- **AC 2: Search**: Highlights matching text in yellow. Automatically opens closed accordions/code tabs/sections to show search matches.
- **AC 3: Q&A Accordions**: Expand/collapse dropdowns. Questions styled dark red (`#b91c1c`), answers dark blue (`#1e3a8a`).
- **AC 4: Code Blocks**: Mock terminal frame, copying copyable text (changes label to "Copied!" for 2 seconds), and file tab switches working instantly. Prism syntax highlighting must render cleanly.
- **AC 5: Borders & Theme Colors**: Outlines on all 4 sides of elements:
  - `.section`, `.sec`: `border: 2.5px solid var(--pc, #6C5CE7) !important;`
  - Sub-cards (`.kc-card`, `.oneliner`): `border: 2px solid #534AB7 !important;`
  - Checklist boxes: `border: 2px solid #16a34a !important;`
  - Q&A boxes (`.qi`): `border: 2px solid #0d9488 !important;`
- **AC 7: Readability**: Use high-contrast CSS colors (WCAG AA). Inline keywords outside of code blocks must use `<span class="hl-kw">`.

---

## ⚠️ 3. KNOWN BUGS & HOW TO AVOID REGRESSIONS

To prevent recurring bugs in the learning portal pages:

### A. CSS Stacking Bug (Multiple visible sections)
- Keep this exact override block in every page's `<style>` tag to prevent multiple session panels from displaying at once:
  ```css
  html body div.section { display: none !important; }
  html body div.section.active { display: block !important; }
  html body div.section.visible { display: block !important; }
  ```

### B. Q&A Accordion Double-Toggle Bug
- The global script `portal-enhance.js` automatically binds a click-toggle listener to `.vr-qa-q` (which is compiled from `.qq`).
- **DO NOT** bind a second `DOMContentLoaded` click toggle listener on the page that replicates this function, or the click event will trigger twice and immediately close/hide the accordion.
- To prevent duplicate bindings by `portal-enhance.js`, mark the element synchronously in your script/HTML initialization:
  ```javascript
  // Set dataset.vrQaToggleDone = '1' synchronously during page rendering or before enhance script executes
  document.querySelectorAll('.qq').forEach(q => {
      q.dataset.vrQaToggleDone = '1';
  });
  ```

### C. Prism Highlight Mutation Observer
- Pages with dynamic content must include the Prism mutation observer at the bottom of the body (before `portal-enhance.js`):
  ```javascript
  if (window.Prism) {
      document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
          const observer = new MutationObserver((mutations) => {
              let needsHighlight = false;
              mutations.forEach(m => {
                  if (m.addedNodes.length) {
                      m.addedNodes.forEach(n => {
                          if (n.nodeName === 'PRE' || n.nodeName === 'CODE') needsHighlight = true;
                          if (n.querySelector && n.querySelector('pre')) needsHighlight = true;
                      });
                  }
              });
              if (needsHighlight) { Prism.highlightAll(); }
          });
          observer.observe(document.body, { childList: true, subtree: true });
      });
  }
  ```

---

## 🔍 4. PRE-FLIGHT VERIFICATION PROCEDURES

Before submitting any task, the agent must perform the following checklist:
1. **No Stacking**: Click every session tab and verify that the previous session hides and only the new one displays.
2. **Accordion Check**: Click Q&A items to verify that they open and close properly, and do not double-toggle.
3. **Copy Functionality**: Click the "Copy" buttons in code tabs and verify the text changes to "Copied!".
4. **No Port Openings**: Confirm that no background processes are running or listening on local ports.
